Package Agents

Interface InferenceAgent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicInferenceAgent, BetterInferenceAgent, BlindfoldedAgent, FourNeighbourAgent, PerfectInferenceAgent
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface InferenceAgent
    A general interface for describing different inference/learning agents.

      • learn

        void learn​(Grid kb,
           Point location)
        Attempt to learn about the environment based on one's existing knowledge and current location.
        Parameters:
        kb - The knowledge base (will be updated with what was learned)
        location - The agent's current location

      • propagateInferences

        default boolean propagateInferences​(Grid kb,
                                    Point location)
        Propagates inferences using rules of the Example Inference Agent, while checking for contradictions.
        Parameters:
        kb - The knowledge base (will be mutated by this function)
        location - The location where a sentiment was changed
        Returns:
        Returns false if an inconsistency was found, true otherwise

      • updateNeighborsAsFree

        default boolean updateNeighborsAsFree​(Point adj,
                                      Grid kb)
        Mark all undecided neighbours of a cell as free/unblocked, and continue propagating the changes. Checks for contradictions along the way.
        Parameters:
        adj - The location of the cell whose neighbours will be marked free
        kb - The knowledge base (will be mutated by this function)
        Returns:
        Returns false if an inconsistency was found, true otherwise

        Parameters:

        kb - The knowledge base (will be mutated by this function)
        Returns:
        Returns false if an inconsistency was found, true otherwise
